The first highway bridge between China and Russia is expected to open in October. With a length of 1,283 meters and a width of 14.7 meters, the bridge across the Heilongjiang River stretches from Heihe, a border city in Northeast China's Heilongjiang Province, to the Russian city of Blagoveshchensk. Photo: VCGÂ  
